HEADWORD: Carnary
<hw>Car"na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>carnarium</ets>, fr. <ets>caro</ets>, <ets>carnis</ets>,
flesh.]</ety> <def>A vault or crypt in connection with a church, used as
a repository for human bones disinterred from their original burial
places; a charnel house.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carnassial</ent>⟦br⟧
